messages.text: Do you know how to change a flat tire?
Yeah…why?
bc Danny just pulled over to help out this couple with a flat tire but I don’t think he knows how to do it.
He got out of the car and now the three of them are all gathered around the tire just staring at it.
LOL
OK I’ll help but why are you two out so late?
None of your business…
Where are you?
I don’t know somewhere near 46. 30 minutes outside town maybe.
Oooooh making out in the woods. I see. Nice and isolated.
Let’s try to act like we graduated from fifth grade.
You’re still in your car?
yeah
OK here’s what we’re gonna do.  I’ll explain how to do it.
then you’ll emerge from the car and take charge acting like you knew everything and never needed any help.
People never think I can do anything. Will be good to do just one thing right.
I can see out the back window and they are still doing nothing.
Instructions. One: find the spare tire.  Should be in their trunk.
Two: find the tire iron (thing that gets the flat tire off). Like a big wrench.
Three: find the car jack.
Wait.
Four: use the car jack to lift up the car.
PAUL WAIT. Something is happening at the other car.
Did they get the spare tire on?
I heard shouting.
Something just slammed against one of the doors. I think a window broke. Now I don’t hear anything.
Stay in the car. Do not get out.
I want to see what’s happening.
STAY IN THE CAR.
Do you have the keys?
Danny has them.
What do you see?
It’s really dark. I’m not sure.
Can they see you? Do they know where you are?
I don’t think so.
Can you see anything now?
It looks like they’re opening their trunk but I’m not sure. I can’t see Danny.
I’m calling the police. Where exactly are you?
Can you guess?
They’re starting their car. They never even changed the tire.
Where are you??? Where is Danny???
We went down 46 maybe 20 minutes, then turned onto a county road. North somewhere.
Stay there while I call the police.
I’m so scared.
Danny still hasn’t come back.
What if they
Oh God
Told 911 your location and your car’s description. They’re coming.
They just turned off their car again.
Both front doors opened.
Do you have a gun in the car?
a GUN??? WHAT?? No
Any weapon?
All I see is a flashlight in the glove compartment.
They’re talking outside. They’re getting closer.
The man just rested his hands on the trunk and the car wobbled.
You’re near the woods?
Yes.
You’re going to have to jump out of the car and sprint as fast as you can into the woods.
What about Danny???
You have to worry about yourself.
Just leave him here? What?
The police are coming. I told you.
Are you sure?
Yes
They’re arguing with each other. Someone said open up the car and leave him in there.
GET OUT OF THE CAR AND RUN INTO THE WOODS
If I don’t text back in five minutes you need to come find me.
Run as fast as you can.
Tell me when you’re somewhere safe.
Waiting.
It’s been three minutes. What’s going on?
HELLO??? My heart is pounding through my chest right now.
Five minutes...
Please please please say something.
what did I do
I’m here.
What happened???
They immediately started runig afterme after I left the car
Sry can barely type. Sweating and hands are all jittery
After I jumped out of the car I heard six pops that were so loud.
The bullets hit trees and I ran down a hill and jumped across a creek. I heard one of them fall down and curse.
I’m crouched in a ditch. Praying they don’t find me.
You lost them?
I think so.
You did amazing. This will all be over soon.
It’s so quiet. Just the trickle of the stream.
You’re doing amazing. Just stay put.
I see red flashing lights through the trees.
Finally. The police.
Thanks for helping get me through this.
The police will find Danny. It’s all almost over.
The police are calling to me now. Said they found them. Said Danny’s safe.
So glad. My heart can stop pounding now.
You telling them your story?
Taking Danny to the hospital?
Make sure you ask to see the officers’ badge.
YOU THERE???
No no no no not again.
PLEASE answer
That wanst the polce. Need help. So jittery again.
What’s going on??
As soon as I started walking someone hit me in the back with something hard.
Please tell me you’re safe.
I tore the branch they were holding away and hit them with the flashlight. They fell down. I ran as fast as I could.
Tell me the police are there.
As soon as I started running I heard someone coming after me. I heard a rock slam against a tree as I ran past
You’re safe now right???
I sprinted up the hill toward the road. Toward the lights. I didn’t hear any pops. I think they ran out of bullets.
Are they still down there?
I think so.
And where are you?
I’m with the police. There’s a blanket over me. Danny is concussed but otherwise not bad.
We’re going to the hospital soon
Finally.
I’m never coming out here ever again. Please don’t tell my parents. They can’t know where I was.
They’re going to have to know. You’re not a kid anymore.
You’re a good friend Paul. I was so scared
You survived. You’re strong.
